a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes a b c d :: complex
assumes h0 : "a = Complex (Re 3) (Im 5)"
and h1 : "b = Complex (Re 3) (Im (-5))"
and h2 : "c = a / b"
and h3 : "d = b / a"
shows  "c + d = -16 / 17"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Simplify
\[\frac{3 + 5i}{3 - 5i} + \frac{3 - 5i}{3 + 5i}.\] The final Answer is -\frac{16}{17}
 ### Proof
 We have that \begin{align} \frac{3 + 5i}{3 - 5i} + \frac{3 - 5i}{3 + 5i} &= \frac{(3 + 5i)(3 + 5i)}{(3 - 5i)(3 + 5i)} + \frac{(3 - 5i)(3 - 5i)}{(3 + 5i)(3 - 5i)} \\ &= \frac{9 + 15i + 15i + 25i^2}{9 - 25i^2} + \frac{9 - 15i - 15i + 25i^2}{9 - 25i^2} \\
 &= \frac{9 + 30i - 25 + 9 - 30i - 25}{9 + 25} \\ &= \frac{-32}{34} = \boxed{-\frac{16}{17}}. \end{align}
 *)

theorem
fixes a b c d :: complex
assumes h0 : "a = Complex (Re 3) (Im 5)"
and h1 : "b = Complex (Re 3) (Im (-5))"
and h2 : "c = a / b"
and h3 : "d = b / a"
shows  "c + d = -16 / 17"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
a_0.informal problem: What is the sum of the complex numbers obtained by dividing $(3 + 5i)$ by $(3 - 5i)$ and dividing $(3 - 5i)$ by $(3 + 5i)$? The final answer is $-\frac{16}{17}$.
